The good, the bad and the ugly of 'use v5.36'

use Modern::Perl mostly obsolete, except:
'given' requires no warnings 'experimental'
'switch' must be explicitly enabled: use feature 'switch';

Function::Parameters 
obsolete for in-line subroutine args
still needed for 'method' (053/1/duncan-c-white.pl)

subroutine signatures:
sub foo(&@) ==> sub :prototype(&@)

bit-wise operators: 
^ ==> ^.

classes:
new Foo ==> Foo->new

hash initialization:
%specialcase = {0=>0, 1=>0} ==> %specialcase = (0=>0, 1=>0) 
